description: Creates an environment for a queue that defines how jobs in the queue run.

parameters.name: clientToken
parameters.description: The unique token which the server uses to recognize retries of the same request. This field is autopopulated if not provided.

parameters.name: farmId
parameters.description: The farm ID of the farm to connect to the environment.

parameters.name: queueId
parameters.description: The queue ID to connect the queue and environment.

parameters.name: priority
parameters.description: Sets the priority of the environments in the queue from 0 to 10,000, where 0 is the highest priority (activated first and deactivated last). If two environments share the same priority value, the environment created first takes higher priority.

parameters.name: templateType
parameters.description: The template's file type, JSON or YAML.

parameters.name: template
parameters.description: The environment template to use in the queue.
